<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 17 at 9:58PM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...Icy spots in the Berkshires are possible on untreated roadways
through 11PM...
Temperatures have dropped to 31 - 33 in the Berkshires this
evening as periods of wintry mix have pushed through the region.
With more of the area observing temperatures near freezing,
freezing rain is possible and any freezing rain may lead to icy
conditions, especially on any untreated roads or walkways.
Motorists are advised to use caution tonight.</description>
